title: Fake 'Millennial Proposal' Speaks Volumes About Ruined Life Moments (VIRAL)
text:
Fake 'Millennial Proposal' Speaks Volumes About Ruined Life Moments (VIRAL) posted by Elvis   The bigger the ring, the more likes... right?  
Marriage proposal videos and photos have gotten a little out of control, and this video just proves it. 
Facebook user John Crist posted a video on Valentine's Day that sums up millennial marriage proposals. 
“Because what’s the point of getting engaged if you don’t post it on Instagram? ” Crist says. 
With over 4.5 million views, apparently, everyone else feels like it's as true as we do. Take a look at the full video below!
